Her prayer meet was held a few days ago in Mumbai, attended by several celebrities including Jeetendra, Hrithik Roshan, Saif Ali Khan, Rakesh Roshan, and others. Recently, Zarine’s daughter Farah Khan Ali shared an emotional video from the late actress’ prayer meet on Instagram, in which Sussanne Khan is seen breaking down in tears.
title: Sussanne Khan breaks down at Zarine Khan’s prayer meet

author: ABHAY AND RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: A chilling timeline of the i20 car that exploded near Red Fort reveals its journey from Faridabad, with the driver, Mohammed Umar, strategically waiting in a crowded Delhi area.  CCTV footage tracked the vehicle's movements for hours before the devastating blast, which killed nine and injured thirty. Investigators are scrutinizing over a thousand cameras to determine if Umar acted alone.
title: Delhi blast suspect circled Connaught Place before proceeding to Red Fort

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: SoftBank has divested its entire stake in U.S. chipmaker Nvidia, raising $5.83 billion to fund its substantial "all in" investment in ChatGPT maker OpenAI. This strategic asset monetization, totaling $30 billion for OpenAI, underscores SoftBank's renewed focus on artificial intelligence and its ambition to lead the global AI ecosystem.
title: Big AI exit: Japan’s No. 2 firm sells full Nvidia stake; cites OpenAI among key reasons

author: MANDAKINI SHALYA
description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) may end up playing all their home matches in Pune in IPL-2026, it has been learnt. The shift is a direct fallout of the Chinnaswamy Stadium’s ongoing suspension following the June 4 stampede during RCB’s victory parade.
title: Pune offers to host RCB home ties in Gahunje

author: TNN
description: A government officer's attempt to seize a sand-laden truck on the Gandhinagar-Kalol highway was met with brazen defiance. Members of the sand mining mafia, using bikers and SUVs, intercepted the officer's team, freed the truck, and threatened the officials. The truck was later found dumping its illegal cargo. Police have registered a case.
title: Gujarat highway heist: Sand mafia convoy blocks woman officer, frees truck
